cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the use of bit-interleaved coded modulation with iterative decoding (BICM-ID) over communication channels, which falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), communication (cs.COMM), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a systematic mapping method for multi-dimensional (MD) modulations, which involves signal processing and potentially system control, falling under the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM).
